Slater & Gordon shares went into freefall once again, plunging as much as 21 per cent in early trade on Thursday after chief executive Andrew Grech said the impact of a slower rate of case resolutions in the UK was having a larger impact than expected. If it was any other company, the stock would have fallen further, but the erosion in the company's marker value throughout the year means there is not a lot more damage that can be done.
